1
00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:04,400
我现在宣布你们结为终身伴侣。
I now pronounce you spouses for life.

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:08,750
我说的在经济上帮助他们是认真的。
I meant what I said about helping out, financially.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,150
我有一个同父异母的弟弟。我有一个儿子。
~ I've got a half brother. ~ I've got a son.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,990
我很抱歉。也许我该见见他了。
I am sorry. Perhaps it's time I met him.

5
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:17,470
西莉亚，跟我说说你的家庭。你真的想嫁给我吗?
~ Celia, tell me about your family. ~ Do you really want to marry me?

6
00:00:17,520 --> 00:00:20,030
我从16岁起就想娶你了。
I've wanted to marry you since I was 16.

7
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:22,630
你确定吗?~课程!你可以继续工作了。
~ Are you sure about this? ~ Course! You can get on with your work.

8
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:24,830
我只要半个小时到四十分钟。
I'll only be half an hour, 40 minutes.

9
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:27,790
发生什么事了?凯特被车撞了。
~ What's happened? ~ Kate's been hit by a car.

10
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:31,080
你要不要过来一下，我们聊聊天。
Do you want to come through here and we'll have a chat.

11
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:24,030
菌群。
Flora.

12
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:26,550
~真的吗?你不喜欢吗?
~ Really? ~ Don't you like it?

13
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:29,670
这是……这取决于你。
It's... It's up to you.

14
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:33,590
这不是我们俩的事吗?~是的。当然可以。但是你……你知道的,
~ Isn't it up to both of us? ~ Yes. Of course. But you're... You know,

15
00:01:33,640 --> 00:01:36,270
你在这件事上有更多的发言权。
you've got more say in the matter.

16
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,790
你必须喜欢它。
You've got to like it.

17
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:39,270
我不讨厌它。
I don't dislike it.

18
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:41,190
——弗洛拉·格蕾丝~好吧。
~ Flora Grace. ~ OK.

19
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,470
你听起来不怎么激动啊。
You don't sound thrilled.

20
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,470
不，我是。
No, I am.

21
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:47,070
那你会怎么称呼她?
Well, what would you call her?

22
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,990
我喜欢这个名字。
I like that name.

23
00:01:49,720 --> 00:01:51,950
甜的。好。
Sweet. Good.

24
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,150
所以你不喜欢它。
So you don't like it.

25
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:56,470
不，我知道，就像我说的。我越来越喜欢它了。这很适合她。
No, I do, like I say. It's growing on me. It suits her.

26
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,830
现在很适合她，但她14岁时还适合吗
Well, it suits her now, but will it suit her when she's 14

27
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,510
然后得到意见。
and got opinions.

28
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:02,830
我真的很喜欢它。~好吧，这才是最重要的。
~ I really like it. ~ Well, then, that's all that matters.

29
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,910
你只是说说而已。我不会那样做的。
~ You're just saying that. ~ I wouldn't do that.

30
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,950
如果我觉得这真的很可恶，我就会这么说。
If I thought it was really abhorrent, I'd say so.

31
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:11,150
~相对于轻微的憎恶?~凯特。我们叫她弗洛拉。菌群。
~ As opposed to mildly abhorrent? ~ Kate. We're calling her Flora. Flora.

32
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:13,350
植物恩典。
Flora Grace.

33
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:16,150
当然，有一种人造黄油叫Flora。
There is some margarine called Flora, of course.

34
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,710
你现在让我扫兴了。
You've put me off it now.

35
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,430
不，我没有。
No, I haven't.

36
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:23,540
别那样跟我说话。男人就是这么说话的。
Don't talk to me like that. That's how men talk.

37
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:27,710
~所以你喜欢格蕾丝?~我喜欢弗洛拉。
~ So you do like Grace? ~ I like Flora.

38
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:30,300
你真的不知道。很明显。
You really don't. It's obvious.

39
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:34,870
她是你的孩子。
She's your baby.

40
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:36,230
她是我们的孩子。
She's our baby.

41
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,430
敲门
KNOCK ON DOOR

42
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,680
妈妈?
Mum?

43
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:47,790
灵车来了。
The hearse has arrived.

44
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,510
外面的。
It's outside.

45
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,750
正确的。
Right.

46
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,750
你想让我把孩子带走吗?
Do you want me to take the baby?

47
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,340
不,我……
No, I'll...

48
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,900
谢谢。
Thanks.

49
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:39,270
每件事都有一个季节
To everything there is a season

50
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,190
这是实现世间一切目的的时刻。
and a time to every purpose on earth.

51
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:47,280
出生的时候，死亡的时候。
A time to be born and a time to die.

52
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:55,710
在这最后一幕中，
Here in this last act,

53
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:59,270
悲伤但无所畏惧，
in sorrow but without fear,

54
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:03,510
在爱和感激中，
in love and appreciation,

55
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:10,950
我们提交凯瑟琳·艾比克·麦肯齐-道森
we commit Katherine Abike McKenzie-Dawson

56
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,870
到一个自然的结局。
to a natural end.

57
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,320
小女孩。小甜心。
Little girl. Little sweetheart.

58
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:29,110
你得给这个孩子取个名字。
You are going to have to decide on a name for this baby.

59
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:31,190
菌群。
Flora.

60
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,270
我在出发前就决定了。
I decided just before we set off.

61
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,590
我是弗洛拉·格蕾丝。
It's Flora Grace.

62
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:37,070
真漂亮，卡洛琳。
That's beautiful, Caroline.

63
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,590
谢谢你！
Thank you.

64
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,920
吉妮卡，你想不想…
Ginika, do you want to...

65
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:56,070
那是父亲。不要看。
That's the father. Don't look.

66
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,230
哪一个?
Which one?

67
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:00,590
矮胖的，苍白的，脸上有毛，12点钟方向。
Pudgy, pale, face hair, 12 o'clock.

68
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:02,190
一直朝这边看。
Keeps looking this way.

69
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,190
以前叫格雷格。
Used to be called Greg.

70
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,230
可能现在也是。
Probably still is.

71
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,270
他是个白痴。
He's an idiot.

72
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:09,990
他们经常是。
They often are.

73
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,590
这是另一个。
And here's another one.

74
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:15,790
约翰。你见过凯特的母亲吉妮卡吗?
John. Have you met Ginika, Kate's mother?

75
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,550
她是经济学教授。
She's a professor of economics.

76
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,270
~啊!~在哥伦比亚大学。
~ Ah! ~ At Columbia.

77
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:21,910
天哪，你好!
Gosh, how do you do?

78
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:25,270
可怕的，悲惨的，可怕的情况。
Terrible, tragic, awful situation.

79
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:28,150
我在约克大学讲英语。
I lecture in English at the University of York.

80
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:31,590
不要和加拿大的约克大学搞混了，
Not to be confused with York University, which is in Canada,

81
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,630
显然。
apparently.

82
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,830
你已经飞来了?不，她上了蒸汽包。
~ So you've flown in? ~ No, she got on a steam packet.

83
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:39,270
你是卡罗琳的前任?
You're Caroline's ex?

84
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:41,510
你一定伤心欲绝。我很抱歉。
You must be devastated, heart-broken. I'm so sorry.

85
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,070
你写小说?
You write novels?

86
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:44,990
嗯,是的。我已经出版了一两本。
Well, yes. I've published one or two.

87
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:47,870
杰克·普罗瑟罗，私家侦探，迷失灵魂。
Jack Protheroe, private detective, lost soul.

88
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:50,630
是的!你已经……你读过……
Yes! You've... Have you read...

89
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:53,670
哦，很久以前了。
Oh, a long time ago.

90
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:56,430
我最喜欢的是《闹鬼的人》。
My favourite is The Haunted Man.

91
00:05:56,480 --> 00:06:01,470
它很有趣，很有趣，很有见地。你很聪明。
It's entertaining, it's interesting, it's insightful. You're very clever.

92
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,190
~天哪，嗯，那是……~爸爸?爸爸!
~ Gosh, well, that's... ~ Dad? Dad!

93
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,870
你得挪一下你的车。你把别人挡在里面了。
You need to move your car. You've blocked someone in.

94
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:10,020
她把手提包落在火葬场了。
She's left her handbag at the crematorium.

95
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:13,460
你能失陪一下吗?~肯定。
~ Would you excuse me? ~ Sure.

96
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,270
那会让他很开心的。
That'll have made his day.

97
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:20,260
你不喜欢他。
You don't like him.

98
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:23,710
我不喜欢凯特的丈夫理查德。
I didn't like Kate's husband, Richard.

99
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:26,390
我母亲不喜欢我的第一任丈夫，
My mother didn't like my first husband,

100
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:29,190
道格拉斯，那个患老年痴呆症的人。
Douglas, the one with Alzheimer's.

101
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:32,180
也许这很正常。也许这是一件事。
Maybe it's normal. Maybe it's a thing.

102
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,830
你母亲喜欢你的第一任丈夫吗?
Did your mother like your first husband?

103
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,230
肯尼斯?
Kenneth?

104
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:40,350
她把他想得神魂颠倒，
She thought the world of him,

105
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:43,640
但如果她知道我对他的了解就不会这么做了
but she wouldn't have done if she had known the things I knew about him.

106
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:47,350
我喜欢卡洛琳。
I like Caroline.

107
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:50,230
我很喜欢凯特。
I was very fond of Kate.

108
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:53,190
有时晚上她会过来和我玩拼字游戏，
She'd come round and play Scrabble with me sometimes in the evening,

109
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,470
当我独自一人的时候
when I was on my own.

110
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:59,550
一开始我觉得很难，
I found it difficult at first,

111
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:05,950
我并不总是那么善良，但是…
and I wasn't always as kind as I might have been, but...

112
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:10,110
这是一个惊喜。嗯，说实话，不完全是这样。
~ It was a surprise. ~ Well, not entirely, if I'm being honest.

113
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,430
凯特很高兴
Kate was very happy

114
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,150
卡洛琳。
with Caroline.

115
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:18,040
大多数时候。~我知道。
~ Most of the time. ~ I know.

116
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:24,600
弗洛拉·格蕾丝。
So, Flora Grace.

117
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:29,440
我知道凯特肯定会喜欢的。
Well, I know for a fact Kate would've liked that.

118
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:36,630
你好。对不起。
Hello. Sorry.

119
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,870
我知道我们合不来，
I know we didn't hit it off,

120
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:41,120
但我不能不来。
but I couldn't not come.

121
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:45,000
除了别的，我们是大学朋友，所以…
We were college buddies, apart from anything else, so...

122
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:49,580
怎么样……我知道我不该问…
How's... I know I'm not supposed to ask...

123
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:53,750
~ . .孩子怎么样了?她很好。
~ .. but how's the baby? ~ She's fine.

124
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,510
她很好。
She's fine.

125
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,670
~女孩?~是的。
~ A girl? ~ Yes.

126
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,230
我不能看她一眼，对吧?
I couldn't have a look at her, could I?

127
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:03,000
这不是计划，是吗?~没有。
~ That wasn't the plan, was it? ~ No.

128
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:07,590
~她会怎么样?她会没事的。
~ What's going to happen to her? ~ She's going to be fine.

129
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,630
~你是…我在照顾她。
~ Are you... ~ I'm looking after her.

130
00:08:09,680 --> 00:08:11,750
~那是……~官方?是的。
~ Is that... ~ Official? Yes.

131
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:14,670
出生证明上我是她的父亲。
I'm on the birth certificate as her parent.

132
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:17,430
不，我是想说，这是你想要的吗?
No, I was going to say, is that what you want?

133
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,550
是的。当然是。
Yes. Of course it is.

134
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,310
一定很辛苦。
It must be tough.

135
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:26,230
我是说，这不是你以为你相信的，对吧?
I mean, it's not what you thought you were buying into, is it?

136
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:29,070
你不想让她生孩子现在就剩你一个人了。
You didn't want her to have a baby and now you're the one left with it.

137
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:31,910
我不是不想让她生孩子。
Well, I didn't not want her to have a baby.

138
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:33,790
对不起，我一定是误解了。
Sorry, I must've misunderstood.

139
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,590
我想要她想要的。
I wanted what she wanted.

140
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:37,510
她说你不像她那么热心。
She said you weren't as keen as she was.

141
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:40,660
我没有，但我也不会阻止她。
I wasn't, but I wouldn't have stopped her.

142
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:43,310
我很抱歉。
I'm sorry.

143
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:46,720
我得走了。我得搭回曼彻斯特的火车。
I'd better go. I've got to get the train back to Manchester.

144
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,670
我只是…
I just...

145
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:53,310
我只想说，
I wanted just to say,

146
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:56,030
看得出来你得到了很多帮助和支持，
I can see you've got a lot of help and support,

147
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:59,470
但是，如果你只是想找人照顾她一会儿或者……
but, if you just wanted someone to look after her for a bit or...

148
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:02,510
就像我说的，在其他情况下
And, as I say, under any other circumstances

149
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,430
我不会提供的。我早就退让了。
I wouldn't be offering. I'd have backed off.

150
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:07,590
我就不会在这里了。这是约定，我很清楚，
I wouldn't even be here. That was the deal and I'm aware of that,

151
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:09,910
但是，如果有什么，
but, if ever there was anything,

152
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:14,070
我很灵活，我是自由职业者，我可以在任何地方工作，
I'm flexible, I'm self-employed, I can work anywhere,

153
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:16,590
所以我不想让你觉得你不能开口
so I wouldn't want you to feel like you couldn't ask

154
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:20,200
或者它会带来不便，因为很可能它不会带来不便。
or that it'd be inconvenient, because chances are it wouldn't be.

155
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,560
~就这些。~好吧。
~ That's all. ~ OK.

156
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,550
好的，谢谢你。
Well, thank you.

157
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,990
有你…你有我的电话号码吗?
Have you... Have you got my number?

158
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:30,310
它……
It...

159
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:34,350
会发到凯特的手机上。
It'll be on Kate's phone.

160
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,240
嗯…
Well...

161
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,030
她在厨房里
She's in the kitchen

162
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:46,790
和我妈妈或者凯特的妈妈一起，如果你愿意的话
with my mum or Kate's mum if you want to

163
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:48,710
看看她。
have a look at her.

164
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,350
我不该问的。
I shouldn't have asked.

165
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:53,140
这取决于你。
It's up to you.

166
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:56,840
好的。
OK.

167
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:03,590
问题是，她和凯特的妈妈在一起
Thing is, she's with Kate's mother

168
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:07,160
凯特的妈妈觉得我是个白痴
and Kate's mother thinks I'm an idiot.

169
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:12,310
一茶匙发酵粉，一勺牛奶，
A teaspoonful of baking powder, a splash of milk,

170
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:15,670
一滴香草精就万事大吉了。
a drop of vanilla essence and bob's your uncle.

171
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:18,270
妈妈。Ginika。
Mum. Ginika.

172
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:20,280
我是格雷格。~你好。
~ This is Greg. ~ Hi.

173
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,270
格雷格的…
